  "text": "Character accuracy based on character position As previously mentioned, an Arabic character may have one to four shapes depending on its position in a word; for example, see Table I . The four possible shapes are isolated, initial, middle and end. Thus, it is valuable to analyse the effectiveness of Arabic OCR systems in recognising isolated, initial, middle and end characters. To analyse accuracy, Arabic characters have been categorised into isolated, initial, middle and end classes by [CITATION_1] , as shown in Table I . The accuracy of each class is determined by equation (1).",
